#!/usr/bin/env perl

use v5.40;
use lib 'lib';
use Ovid::App::LiveEditor;
use Dancer2;
use Path::Tiny;
use Getopt::Long;
use Browser::Open;
use HTTP::Tiny;
use Time::HiRes qw(sleep);

my $port = 3000;

GetOptions(
    'port=i' => \$port,
) or die "Usage: $0 [--open] [--port=N] <file>\n";

my $file = shift @ARGV or die "Usage: $0 [--open] [--port=N] <file>\n";
my $path = path($file)->absolute;

# Auto-correct generated files to source files
# If user provides blog/foo.html, switch to root/blog/foo.tt
if ( $path =~ m{/(?:articles|blog)/.*\.html$} ) {
    my $root = path('.')->absolute;
    my $rel  = eval { $path->relative($root) };
    if ( !$@ && $rel !~ /^\.\./ ) {

        # Try .tt
        my $base_path = $root->child('root')->child($rel);
        my $try_tt    = $base_path->stringify;
        $try_tt =~ s/\.html$/.tt/;

        if ( -f $try_tt ) {
            my $p = path($try_tt);
            say STDERR "Notice: You provided a generated file. Switching to source file: " . $p->relative($root);
            $path = $p;
        }
        else {
            # Try .tt2markdown
            my $try_md = $try_tt . "2markdown";
            if ( -f $try_md ) {
                my $p = path($try_md);
                say STDERR "Notice: You provided a generated file. Switching to source file: " . $p->relative($root);
                $path = $p;
            }
        }
    }
}

die "File not found: $path\n" unless $path->exists;
die "Path is a directory, not a file: $path\n" if $path->is_dir;
die "File is not readable: $path\n" unless -r $path;

# Ensure file is within the project root (basic security check)
my $project_root = path('.')->absolute;
if ( $path->stringify !~ /^\Q$project_root\E/ ) {
    die "Security Error: Cannot edit files outside the project directory.\n";
}

$ENV{LIVE_EDITOR_FILE} = $path->stringify;

# Security: Bind to localhost only
set host => '127.0.0.1';
set port => $port;

my $pid = fork();
if ( !defined $pid ) {
    warn "Failed to fork for browser launch: $!";
}
elsif ( $pid == 0 ) {

    # Child process
    if ( open my $fh, '>>', 'child_debug.log' ) { print $fh "Child $$ started\n"; close $fh; }

    my $url        = "http://127.0.0.1:$port/";
    my $health_url = "http://127.0.0.1:$port/health";
    my $http       = HTTP::Tiny->new( timeout => 1 );

    # Poll for server readiness
    my $max_retries = 50;    # 5 seconds
    for ( 1 .. $max_retries ) {
        my $resp = $http->get($health_url);
        if ( $resp->{success} ) {
            my $err = Browser::Open::open_browser($url);
            if ( defined $err ) {
                warn "Failed to open browser: exit code $err";
            }
            exit 0;
        }
        sleep 0.1;
    }
    warn "Server did not become ready in time (5s). Open $url manually.";
    exit 0;
}

# Parent continues to start server

dance;

__END__

=head1 NAME

launch - Start the live editor for editing blog posts and articles

=head1 SYNOPSIS

    perl bin/launch [OPTIONS] <file>

    # Edit an article with default port (3000)
    perl bin/launch root/articles/my-article.tt

    # Edit a blog post on custom port
    perl bin/launch --port=3001 root/blog/my-post.tt

    # Works with .tt2markdown files too
    perl bin/launch root/blog/my-post.tt2markdown

    # Auto-corrects if you provide generated HTML
    perl bin/launch blog/my-post.html
    # Notice: Switching to source file: root/blog/my-post.tt

=head1 DESCRIPTION

The C<launch> script starts a live editor server for editing Template Toolkit
files. It provides a side-by-side editing experience with real-time preview of
your content as you type.

The editor runs a Dancer2 web application (L<Ovid::App::LiveEditor>) that serves:

=over 4

=item * A CodeMirror-based editor with syntax highlighting

=item * Real-time Markdown preview

=item * Auto-save functionality (saves after 1 second of inactivity)

=item * Image upload with automatic resizing

=item * Vim mode support (toggleable)

=item * Dark mode support (toggleable)

=item * File browser for navigating between templates

=back

The script automatically opens your default browser to the editor interface once
the server is ready.

=head1 OPTIONS

=over 4

=item B<--port=N>

Specify the port number for the server. Default is 3000.

    perl bin/launch --port=8080 root/blog/my-post.tt

=back

=head1 ARGUMENTS

=over 4

=item B<file>

Path to the Template Toolkit file to edit. Can be:

=over 8

=item * Relative path: C<root/blog/my-post.tt>

=item * Absolute path: C</Users/username/website/root/articles/foo.tt>

=item * Generated HTML (auto-corrected): C<blog/my-post.html> → C<root/blog/my-post.tt>

=item * Either C<.tt> or C<.tt2markdown> extensions

=back

The file must exist within the project directory for security reasons.

=back

=head1 AUTO-CORRECTION

If you accidentally provide a generated HTML file path (e.g., C<blog/foo.html>),
the script will automatically find and use the corresponding source template:

    # You provide: blog/foo.html
    # Script uses: root/blog/foo.tt

    # Or if that doesn't exist:
    # Script uses: root/blog/foo.tt2markdown

This is convenient when you're browsing the generated site and want to quickly
edit the source.

=head1 SECURITY

The server is bound to C<127.0.0.1> (localhost) only and cannot be accessed from
other machines. This is a security feature to prevent unauthorized access to your
content.

The script also validates that the file path is within the project directory to
prevent path traversal attacks.

=head1 EDITOR FEATURES

=head2 Auto-Save

Content is automatically saved to disk after 1 second of typing inactivity. You'll
see a "Typing..." indicator while typing and "Saved" when the save completes.

=head2 Keyboard Shortcuts

=over 4

=item * C<Ctrl-S> or C<Cmd-S> - Manually trigger save and refresh preview

=back

=head2 Vim Mode

Toggle vim mode from the dropdown menu (☰). When enabled:

=over 4

=item * Standard vim keybindings (hjkl, dd, yy, p, etc.)

=item * Mode indicator shows current mode (NORMAL, INSERT, VISUAL)

=item * Preference persisted in browser localStorage

=item * Key repeat works naturally after initial delay

=back

=head2 Image Upload

From the dropdown menu, select "Upload Image" to:

=over 4

=item * Upload PNG, GIF, or JPG images

=item * Images automatically resized to max 300KB

=item * Saved to C<root/static/images/>

=item * Template snippet inserted at cursor position

=item * Supports drag-and-drop and paste from clipboard

=back

=head2 Dark Mode

Toggle dark mode from the dropdown menu. Uses Monokai theme for CodeMirror when
enabled. Preference persisted in browser localStorage.

=head2 File Browser

Click "Edit Post" from the dropdown menu to browse and switch between all template
files in the C<root/> directory.

=head1 IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS

=over 4

=item 1. The script validates the file path and sets C<$ENV{LIVE_EDITOR_FILE}>

=item 2. Forks a child process to monitor server startup

=item 3. Child polls C</health> endpoint every 100ms (max 5 seconds)

=item 4. Once server is ready, child opens default browser

=item 5. Parent process starts the Dancer2 application

=back

The Dancer2 app provides these endpoints:

=over 4

=item * C<GET /> - Editor interface

=item * C<POST /api/save> - Save content

=item * C<GET /preview> - Rendered preview

=item * C<GET /api/files> - List all template files

=item * C<POST /api/upload-image> - Upload and resize images

=item * C<GET /health> - Health check for startup polling

=back

=head1 EXIT STATUS

=over 4

=item 0

Success - server started and running

=item 1

Error - invalid arguments, file not found, or security violation

=back

=head1 EXAMPLES

    # Basic usage
    perl bin/launch root/blog/my-new-post.tt

    # Custom port (useful if 3000 is in use)
    perl bin/launch --port=5000 root/articles/tutorial.tt

    # Edit from anywhere in the project
    cd some/subdirectory
    perl ../../bin/launch ../../root/blog/post.tt

    # Quick edit from generated file
    perl bin/launch articles/my-article.html
    # → Automatically switches to root/articles/my-article.tt

=head1 TROUBLESHOOTING

=over 4

=item B<"Server did not become ready in time">

The server took longer than 5 seconds to start. Try:

=over 8

=item * Check if port is already in use: C<lsof -i :3000>

=item * Try a different port: C<--port=3001>

=item * Open the URL manually (shown in the warning)

=back

=item B<"Security Error: Cannot edit files outside the project directory">

You're trying to edit a file outside the project root. The editor only allows
editing files within the project for security.

=item B<"File not found">

The specified file doesn't exist. Check the path and ensure it's a C<.tt> or
C<.tt2markdown> file in the C<root/> directory.

=item B<Browser doesn't open automatically>

The browser should open automatically within 5 seconds. If not:

=over 8

=item * Manually navigate to C<http://127.0.0.1:3000/>

=item * Check that Browser::Open is installed: C<cpanm Browser::Open>

=item * Check C<child_debug.log> for errors

=back

=back

=head1 DEPENDENCIES

=over 4

=item * L<Ovid::App::LiveEditor> - The Dancer2 application

=item * L<Dancer2> - Web framework

=item * L<Path::Tiny> - File path handling

=item * L<Getopt::Long> - Command-line option parsing

=item * L<Browser::Open> - Automatic browser launching

=item * L<HTTP::Tiny> - Health check polling

=item * L<Time::HiRes> - Sub-second sleep delays

=back

=head1 FILES

=over 4

=item C<child_debug.log>

Debug log for the browser-launching child process. Created in the current directory.

=item C<root/>

Directory containing all template files that can be edited.

=item C<root/static/images/>

Destination directory for uploaded images.

=back

=head1 SEE ALSO

=over 4

=item * L<Ovid::App::LiveEditor> - The live editor Dancer2 application

=item * L<bin/article> - Create new articles and blog posts

=item * L<bin/rebuild> - Rebuild the entire site

=item * L<Template::Plugin::Blogdown> - Markdown processing for content

=back

